  "prompt": "How did Stitch Fix start?",
  "response": "Stitch Fix was founded in 2011 by Katrina Lake. The idea for the company came from Lake's passion for fashion and her desire to create a more personalized shopping experience. She wanted to leverage data and technology to curate personalized clothing recommendations for customers, hence combining the art of personal styling with the science of data analytics. Lake started Stitch Fix while she was a student at Harvard Business School and grew the company from a small startup to a successful public corporation. The service allows customers to receive a curated selection of clothing and accessories, chosen specifically for them by professional stylists, based on their style preferences, sizing, and other personal factors.",
